dict.string: Set them in Alfred Preferences at Top

source bash_functions P=`echo "{query}" | sed "s/ /-/g"` cp -r templates/project-files ~/Dropbox/projects/$P-files mv ~/Dropbox/projects/$P-files/notes.md ~/Dropbox/projects/$P-files/$P-notes.md tags -add p-$P ~/Dropbox/projects/$P-files/$P-notes.md tags -add p-$P ~/Dropbox/projects/$P-files tags -add project-files ~/Dropbox/projects/$P-files rm -rf ~/active mkdir ~/active
# Link the main files directory so we can access the settings.yml file inside ln -s ~/Dropbox/projects/$P-files ~/active/files
# Get Site Root P_SITE_ROOT=`osascript -e 'set source_folder to choose folder with prompt "Please select the Site Root directory."
tell application "System Events" set item_list to POSIX path of source_folder end tell'` if [ "$P_SITE_ROOT" ] then addsetting site_root $P_SITE_ROOT fi
# Get Theme Root P_THEME=`osascript -e 'set source_folder to choose folder with prompt "Please select the Theme directory."
tell application "System Events" set item_list to POSIX path of source_folder end tell'` if [ "$P_THEME" ] then addsetting theme $P_THEME fi
# Get Google Docs directory P_GDOCS=`osascript -e 'set source_folder to choose folder with prompt "Please select the Google Docs directory."
tell application "System Events" set item_list to POSIX path of source_folder end tell'` if [ "$P_GDOCS" ] then addsetting gdocs $P_GDOCS fi
sh setup-folders.sh open ~/Dropbox/projects/$P-files /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -message "$P Project Made. Site Root Next."
Select a project to switch focus to, type * to see all.

source bash_functions /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -message "Shutting downâ€¦" -title "Project Helper" sh ~/active/files/scripts/shutdown.sh rm -rf ~/active mkdir ~/active ln -s "{query}" ~/active/files sh setup-folders.sh "{query}" /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -message "Please run (,p start) in Alfred" -title "Active Project Switched" /usr/bin/osascript -e 'tell application "Alfred 2" to search ",p start"'
source bash_functions replacesetting gdocs "{query}" rm -rf ~/active/docs ln -s "{query}" ~/active/docs
source bash_functions rdef ~/projects/settings.yml browser echo "browser: {query}" >> ~/projects/settings.yml echo "Development Browser Set"
source bash_functions addsetting site_root "{query}" rm -rf ~/active/site-root ln -s "{query}" ~/active/site-root
rm -rf ~/active/links ln -s "{query}" ~/active/links echo "Links Directory set to {query}"
rm -rf ~/active/assets ln -s "{query}" ~/active/assets echo "Assets Directory set to {query}"
rm -rf ~/active/files/scripts ln -s "{query}" ~/active/files/scripts echo "Scripts Directory set to {query}"
source bash_functions replacesetting theme "{query}" rm -rf ~/active/theme ln -s "{query}" ~/active/theme
rm -rf ~/active/files ln -s "{query}" ~/active/files echo "Files Directory set to {query}"
source bash_functions rdef ~/active/files/settings.yml notes echo "notes: {query}" >> ~/active/files/settings.yml echo "Notes File set to {query}"
Find Assets in Active Project (Comps, Wireframes, etc)
Show SASS files in Active Project's Theme

PROJECT="`ls -l ~/active | grep files | sed 's,^.*projects/,,' | sed 's,files,,'`" /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -message "You're on $PROJECT. Click to view." -execute "open ~/active"
cd ~/active/site-root && git pull && git push && /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -message "Git Push Done (after pulling)"
Git Push in Site Root (after pulling)
cd ~/active/site-root && git pull && /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -message "Git Pull Done"
cd ~/active/theme /opt/local/bin/drush cc all && /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -message "Drupal Cache Cleared!" -title "Project Helper"
Pass in what command you want to start a new Terminal window in (include `ssh`)

SSH="$(cat ~/active/files/settings.yml | grep ^ssh_staging: | sed "s/ssh_staging: //")" terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -subtitle "$SSH" -message "Click to edit" -execute "open ~/active/files/settings.yml" $SSH
SSH into Staging. Hold CMD for Production.

SSH="$(cat ~/active/files/settings.yml | grep ^ssh_prod: | sed "s/ssh_prod: //")" terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -subtitle "$SSH" -message "Click to edit" -execute "open ~/active/files/settings.yml" $SSH

cd ~/active/site-root RSYNC="$(cat ~/active/files/settings.yml | grep ^rsync_staging: | sed "s/rsync_staging: //")" terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -subtitle "$RSYNC" -message "Click to edit" -execute "open ~/active/files/settings.yml" $RSYNC /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -message "Done" -title "Project Helper" -subtitle "Drush Files Rsync Done" afplay /System/Library/Sounds/Submarine.aiff
Launch Custom Shell Scripts for Active Project in Site Root. Hold CMD for Backgrounding.
Set dev URL, hold CMD for staging, option for production
Open files, folders, and URLs that have been set.
Set stuff to open at start

echo "open \"{query}\"" >> ~/active/files/scripts/open-at-start.sh terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -subtitle "will open now" -message "Click to view current list to open" -execute "open ~/active/files/scripts/open-at-start.sh"

cd ~/active/theme sh ~/active/files/scripts/start-in-theme.sh terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -subtitle "Theme Scripts Done" -message "Click to Edit" -execute "open -t ~/projects/scripts/start-in-theme.sh"
Run the Start in Site Root & Theme Scripts

cd ~/active/site-root sh ~/active/files/scripts/start-in-site-root.sh terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -subtitle "Site Root Scripts Done" -message "Click to Edit" -execute "open -t ~/active/files/scripts/start-in-site-root.sh"

source ~/.bash_profile sh ~/active/files/scripts/open-at-start.sh terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -subtitle "Done opening" -message "Click to edit" -execute "open ~/active/files/scripts/open-at-start.sh"
Search settings file for 'Question: Answer' by passing in Question. Seperate words with .*

QUESTION=$(echo "{query}" | sed "s/ /\.\*/") # NOTES=$(cat ~/active/files/settings.yml | grep ^notes: | sed "s/notes: //") # ANSWER=$(cat "$NOTES" | grep "\w*:\s" | grep -i "$QUESTION") ANSWER=`cat ~/active/files/settings.yml | grep "\w*:\s" | grep -i "$QUESTION"` echo "$ANSWER" | sed "s/.*: //" | tr -d '\n' | pbcopy if [$ANSWER = ""] then echo "Answer not found" else echo "Answer in clipboard" fi
# @todo close all SourceTree windows first open ~/active/site-root -a SourceTree
Drupal Admin password set to "{query}" and copied.
Reset Drupal password by passing in a new password.

## Suggested Utilities
If you install Terminal Notifier, the workflow can provide you with richer notifications.
gem install terminal-notifier
